SEO Crawl System
----------------
Primary user crawl route:
- POST /api/seo/run

Status polling:
- GET /api/seo/run-status?crawlRunId=...

Webhook:
- POST /api/seo/webhook

Important behavior:
- /api/seo/run starts Apify and creates a running scans row.
- webhook fetches Apify dataset, normalizes/enriches, persists crawl pages/reports/issues.
- zero-page imports fail instead of pretending to create a usable report.
- validated SEO reads require stored page URLs to match the website primary domain.
- response-code report reads are tied to the validated latest crawl.
- AI SEO recommendations return no_crawl_data when there are no saved page rows.
- AI SEO recommendations use a fast model first and timeout to deterministic crawl-based advice.
- UI avoids duplicate crawl buttons and uses one primary SEO Crawl path.

